Burnley host Tottenham in the Premier League on Sunday . 
  Michael Duff is the second oldest outfield player in the league behind Sylvain Distin . 
  The 37-year-old defender has played in eight different divisions and was told his career was over in 2007 . 
  Duff will be tasked with stopping Harry Kane at Turf Moor . 
  The defender is the only survivor of promotion and relegation . 
 